            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1946-10-15T17:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1946-07-28T18:00:00-05:00" n="211" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d211">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">C.P.(Gen)Doc.1.J.34.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Article 32</hi>
                </head>
                <dateline>
                    <date ana="#date_undated-inferred-from-outside-research" calendar="gregorian" notAfter="1946-10-15T23:59:59+01:00" notBefore="1946-07-29T00:00:00+01:00">undated</date>
                </dateline>
                <p>After Article 32 add a new article 32 bis reading as follows: <list>
                        <label>1.</label>
                        <item>
                            <hi rend="italic">Bulgaria undertakes to cede within three months from
                                the date of entry into force of the present Treaty a free zone on
                                the Danube</hi> (<hi rend="italic">Port of Lom</hi>) <hi rend="italic">equipped at her own expense for transit
                            trade</hi>.</item>
                        <label>2.</label>
                        <item>
                            <hi rend="italic">A special commission of experts composed of
                                representatives of Greece, Bulgaria, Hungary and Roumania, convened
                                within the month following the entry into force of the present
                                Treaty, under the chairmanship of a neutral member, chosen by the
                                Economic Commission of the United Nations, will proceed to draw up
                                the main technical, economic and administrative clauses governing
                                the operation under conditions of complete equality of the Free Zone
                                and of its port and railroad facilities</hi>.</item>
                        <label>3.</label>
                        <item>
                            <hi rend="italic">Any dispute concerning the interpretation of the above
                                paragraphs will be referred, on the request of the interested party,
                                to an arbitrator designated by the Economic Commission of the United
                                Nations whose ruling will be final</hi>.</item>
                    </list>
                </p>
            </div>
        </body>
